OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1778163069
OL,3,CWetherspoons boss attacks Ryanair's
OL,4,Ccall to limit airport drinking
OL,6,FCivil Aviation Authority figures show
OL,7,Fincidents involving disruptive
OL,8,Fpassengers have risen since the
OL,9,Fpandemic.
OL,11,FUnlike normal pubs, airside venues are
OL,12,Fexempt from standard alcohol licensing
OL,13,Fhours. O'Leary said airport alcohol
OL,14,Frules should more closely match those
OL,15,Fapplying to pubs elsewhere.
OL,17,FIt is a criminal offence to be drunk
OL,18,Fon an aircraft, and it's punishable
OL,19,Fwith a large fine and up to two years
OL,20,Fin prison.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/6
